35. The Third kind of Light in the mind is the Aequired Light, the Light of Learning. And this is the supplement of the other two ; and is derb-ed by meditation or by teaehing from the other two, the Light of Nature and of Scripture. The two principal means thereof are the Discourse of Reason, and the Authority of the Church, in- cluding her judgment and her practice.
